Ich hatte eine Zeit lang diese App nicht benutzt, da die virtuell gepflanzten Bäume ein wenig zu empfindlich bei meinem alten Handy waren. Dort war es so, dass selbst bei einer Push Benachrichtung von Whats App mein Baum starb. Mit meinem jetzigen Handy habe ich das Problem nicht, es macht sehr Spaß Bäume zu pflanzen. Meine Freunde und ich erstellen oft Räume zu Vorlesungen und erhöhen unsere Produktivität gemeinsam. Erstaunlicher Weise ist es vor allem in Zeiten von Corona sehr schön mit diesen sogenannten Räumen zu Arbeiten(geht einer an sein Handy sterben auch die Bäume der anderen), da wir uns dadurch uns einander auch wieder näher sind ohne uns zu schreiben. Der kauf der Pro Version ist bei 1,99 Euro auch eine sehr gute Anschaffung. Selbst ne Tüte Bon-Bons ist da ja schon teurer. Man kann dann zum einen mit Freunden pflanzen, echte Bäume pflanzen lassen, Tags erstellen (damit man weiß, wie man die Zeit genutzt hat) und und und.... Eine Empfehlung für alle! Wenn ihr euch die App nun wegen meiner tollen Rezession holt könnt ihr gerne diesen Code eingeben bei dem Menü Freunde einladen, auf das Zeichen gehen das wie ein Coupon aussieht und da meinen Empfehlungscode eingeben: 42FSEG2SG (wäre voll cool dann kriege ich ein Birnenbaumhaus wenn das genug machen *___*)

Excellent way to reclaim productivity. Several features to track non-phone time. You select a tree type & time length then 'plant'. A virtual tree grows during that time frame with an option to have the tree die if you touch your phone (if you need the extra encouragement). TOTALLY worth the purchase price for me.

This is one of my favorite apps. It has greatly helped my ability to focus. Like many people these days, I checked my phone very frequently; you could say it was obsessive. I scrolled mindlessly on my phone, not really sure what I was looking for. Furthermore, all the doom and gloom on the news probably worsened this feeling. I had trouble focusing on any task, whether it was work or pleasure, because I kept checking my phone. Well, Forest helps you with that. The app is disarmingly simple: you select a plant and set a timer and...put your phone down. After you successfully did not check your phone, the plant you selected gets planted into your forest. If you fail and check your phone, your plant dies and you have to start over. Your forest grows the more times you set the timer and successfully wait. You also earn points for focusing which you can then use to "buy" (you're using an in-game currency) other cute plants and trees, like a weeping willow or a sunflower. These are really cute and it gives you an incentive to continue focusing. It takes a while to accumulate points which I actually like; it may take you a week or so to unlock a new plant. Alternatively, you have the option to donate your unused points to plant real trees somewhere in the world, which is a great idea. In all, the app has helped me to avoid distractions and that has helped my mental health. I am more intentional with my phone now. I think of what my phone can do for me; otherwise, I set the timer and put it down. The paid version is a one-time purchase of $1.99 and I think it's definitely worth it. You'll unlock more features that make the experience more pleasant. If anyone is struggling to focus because of their phone use, then this app will definitely help you. Go plant a virtual forest!

This is it. This is the productivity app that I've been looking for. I've tried many and they are either too dull and simple or too complicated and too engaging (e.g. apps that gamify productivity with so many settings that customising your productivity app settings becomes a time sink...). This brilliantly addictive app tows the fine line between being too simple/dull or too complex/engaging perfectly. Perhaps the app's most endearing feature is that you can have a goal of growing a particular specific themed garden for a particular week/month/year. This is pretty much heroine for a perfectionist and having this perfectionist drive tied to actual productivity rather than stupid useless stuff I get sucked into is simply glorious. One thing I wish they change is to prevent the firefox extension and the app from both growing trees at the same time.

I'm also really interested in the "plant a real tree" initiative. CON- unless you pay for the full app, calls, messages, and alarms will make your bush/tree DIE. I decided to pay (very cheap), and the full app allows you to White List calls, messages, alarms, and as many apps as you want. It is very worth it.
